Task 3 — Image Processor Factory

🎯 Objective:
Build a Spring Core application where a FactoryBean dynamically provides different types of image processors.

📌 Requirements:

Define an ImageProcessor interface with a process() method.

Implement three processors:

ResizeProcessor

FilterProcessor

WatermarkProcessor

Create an ImageProcessorFactoryBean that returns the correct processor implementation based on a property value (e.g., image.operation).

Configure the factory in Spring and test by retrieving the bean and invoking process().

✅ Expected Output:

If image.operation=resize
Image resized successfully!